👉 The throw Keyword

The throw Keyword is used to throw an exception explicitly by the programmer

if(b==0){
    throw new ArithmeticException("Div By 0");
}else{
    return a/b;
}

In a Similar manner, we can throw user defined exceptions :
                                                            throw new MyException("Exception thrown");

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

👉 Throw v/s Throws in JAVA

throw (Used to actually throw an exception)
Used inside a method
Throws one exception at a time
Followed by an object (new keyword)
Used when you want to manually create an exception

throws (Used to declare exceptions)
Used in method declaration
Can declare multiple exceptions
Tells compiler:
                “This method might throw these exceptions”
Does not throw, just informs

